
[1]disturbance

   DISTURBANCE, n.

   1. A stirring or excitement; any disquiet or interruption of peace; as,
   to enter the church without making disturbance.

   2. Interruption of a settled state of things; disorder; tumult. We have
   read much at times of disturbances in Spain, England and Ireland.

   3. Emotion of the mind; agitation; excitement of passion; perturbation.
   The merchant received the news of his losses without apparent
   disturbance.

   4. Disorder of thoughts; confusion.

   They can survey a variety of complicated ideas, without fatigue or
   disturbance.

   5. In law, the hindering or disquieting of a person in the lawful and
   peaceable enjoyment of his right; the interruption of a right; as the
   disturbance of a franchise, of common, of ways, of tenure, of
   patronage.
